Proposed law extends that period to 30 business days.
Present law provides that a covered financial institution may extend the delay following a
request from a covered agency to no more than 25 business days from the date on which the
covered financial institution first initiated the delay of the financial transaction.
Proposed law extends that period to 45 days.
